column4: tx - I have another question.  I have a friend who's chkrootkit reported a problem with '/usr/bin/find'.  We compared md5sums and mine doesn't match his, yet we are both running Breezy.  Any idea how this can be?
someone reported that the other day too (can't recall the nick)
Do you think it is anything to be concerned about?
i can't say no, but don't know for sure sorry
what was was wrong with !ops? (i think you meant forget homer)
sorry if I deleted that by mistake
I wanted to invoke ops as they do in #debian, but it didn't work
instead it seemed to reset the factoid
can you reset to the original?
I just blew it a kiss :-)
